{#
  Base layout for Siti Agri embedded screen views.

  INTENTIONALLY DIFFERENT FROM GOV.UK DESIGN SYSTEM.
  This template uses a distinct visual style to demonstrate that the
  iframe content comes from a third-party system (Siti Agri).
  In the real system, Siti Agri screens use their own Angular-based UI
  framework with different branding, typography, and layout.

  The visual distinction helps developers understand the boundary between
  portal content (GOV.UK styled) and embedded content (SitiAgri styled).

  POSTMESSAGE SCRIPT:
  Each embedded screen includes a small script that sends the content
  height to the parent page via window.postMessage(). This allows the
  portal to resize the iframe dynamically, eliminating scrollbars and
  creating a seamless visual integration.
#}
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <title>{% block title %}Siti Agri{% endblock %}</title>
  <style>
    /* Intentionally simple styling — NOT GOV.UK Design System.
       This represents the third-party Siti Agri UI styling. */
    * {
      box-sizing: border-box;
      margin: 0;
      padding: 0;
    }
    body {
      font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;
      font-size: 14px;
      line-height: 1.5;
      color: #333;
      padding: 16px;
      background-color: #fafafa;
    }
    .sa-header {
      background-color: #2e7d32;
      color: white;
      padding: 8px 16px;
      margin: -16px -16px 16px -16px;
      font-size: 12px;
    }
    .sa-header small {
      opacity: 0.8;
    }
    h1 {
      font-size: 20px;
      margin-bottom: 16px;
      color: #1b5e20;
    }
    h2 {
      font-size: 16px;
      margin: 16px 0 8px 0;
      color: #2e7d32;
    }
    table {
      width: 100%;
      border-collapse: collapse;
      margin: 12px 0;
    }
    th, td {
      border: 1px solid #ccc;
      padding: 8px 12px;
      text-align: left;
    }
    th {
      background-color: #e8f5e9;
      font-weight: bold;
      font-size: 13px;
    }
    td {
      font-size: 13px;
    }
    .sa-info {
      background-color: #e3f2fd;
      border-left: 4px solid #1976d2;
      padding: 12px;
      margin: 12px 0;
      font-size: 13px;
    }
    .sa-badge {
      display: inline-block;
      padding: 2px 8px;
      border-radius: 3px;
      font-size: 11px;
      font-weight: bold;
      text-transform: uppercase;
    }
    .sa-badge--active { background: #c8e6c9; color: #1b5e20; }
    .sa-badge--pending { background: #fff3e0; color: #e65100; }
    .sa-badge--submitted { background: #e3f2fd; color: #0d47a1; }
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <div class="sa-header">
    <small>Siti Agri — Embedded Screen ({{ application }})</small>
  </div>

  {% block content %}{% endblock %}

  {#
    PostMessage script — communicates content height to the parent page.

    This is how the iframe tells the portal how tall its content is,
    allowing the portal to resize the iframe and eliminate scrollbars.

    SECURITY: We specify the target origin (window.location.origin) in
    the postMessage call. This ensures the message is only delivered to
    pages on the expected origin. In a cross-origin setup, you would
    specify the portal's exact origin instead of '*'.

    MESSAGE FORMAT:
    {
      type: 'embedded-screen-resize',
      height: <number in pixels>
    }
  #}
  <script>
    // Send content height to parent page for iframe resizing.
    // Uses '*' as target origin because in the nginx setup, parent and
    // iframe are same-origin. In cross-origin deployments, replace '*'
    // with the specific portal origin for security.
    function reportHeight() {
      var height = document.documentElement.scrollHeight;
      window.parent.postMessage(
        { type: 'embedded-screen-resize', height: height },
        '*'
      );
    }

    // Report height on load and after any content changes
    window.addEventListener('load', reportHeight);
    // Also report after a short delay to catch dynamic content
    setTimeout(reportHeight, 500);
  </script>
</body>
</html>
